η. Ex municipio Aletrinate. Aletrium, written also Alatrium, as in Greek Ἀλέτριον and Ἀλάτριον, was in the country of the Hernici. a few miles to the north of the Via Latina, about ten miles due east of Anagnia (Anagni), and six miles north of Ferentinum (Ferentino). The modern town Alatri is chiefly interesting from the circumstance that the walls which encompassed the ancient city and its citadel still remain almost entire, presenting perhaps the finest and most perfect example in existence of that very ancient and massive style of building which is now generally termed ‘Polygonal ¹.'
